Start Fresh Cluster - Minikube 
# Delete all deploys on the cluster using command 
minikube delete --all 

# Reset ur cluster back :

#Command for minikube - Cheatsheet
https://cheatsheet.dennyzhang.com/cheatsheet-minikube-a4



To Install minikube on AWS ::
https://www.techbeatly.com/installing-a-kubernetes-cluster-using-minikube/

Download kubectl
curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/release/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"

## Download the kubectl checksum file and Validate
$ curl -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/$(curl -L -s https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt)/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl.sha256"
$ echo "$(<kubectl.sha256) kubectl" | sha256sum --check

## Install 
$ sudo install -o root -g root -m 0755 kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl

# Make the kubectl binary executable.
chmod +x ./kubectl
# Move the binary in to your PATH.
sudo mv ./kubectl /usr/local/bin/kubectl

kubectl version --short

# download and install minikube package
$ curl -LO https://storage.googleapis.com/minikube/releases/latest/minikube-linux-amd64
 
$ sudo install minikube-linux-amd64 /usr/local/bin/minikube

Run with these specs :
sudo minikube start --addons=ingress --cni=flannel --install-addons=true     --kubernetes-version=stable     --vm-driver=docker --wait=false     --cpus=4 --memory=6g --force

## Check addons
$ minikube addons list
$ minikube addons enable metrics-server
$ minikube dashboard

Add your user to the Docker group: Add your user to the Docker group using the following command:
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
